South Africa has recorded 2 893 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 635 465. The cumulative recoveries now stand at 1 539 395 representing a recovery rate of 94,1%. The country has also recorded 30 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Sunday. This brings the total number of deaths to 55 802. The provincial breakdown of deaths, “Eastern Cape 1, Free State 5, Gauteng 20, Kwa-Zulu Natal 1,
Limpopo 0, Mpumalanga 0, North West 0, Northern Cape 0 and Western Cape 3,” according to the Health Department. The number of tests conducted to date is 11 354 930. Of these 29 355 tests were conducted since the
